===Etymology===
Compare {{cog|bo|གཏུག||to meet; to touch}} ({{zh-ref|Hill, 2019}}). An older theory by STEDT compares the word with {{cog|sit-pro|*m/r-tuk|t=to cut, knock, pound}}, and compares the first two syllables of {{cog|my|တောက်တောက်ကြော်|t=fried minced meat}}, as well as a wide range of Sinitic words:
* {{och-l|擣|to beat, pound rice}}
* {{och-l|殊|to cut off, die}}
* {{och-l|祝|to cut off, pray}}
* {{och-l|斵}}, {{och-l|斫|to chop, carve, chisel, break open}}
* {{och-l|椓|to beat, strike}}
* {{och-l|啄|to peck}}
* {{och-l|斀|to castrate}}
* {{och-l|誅|to reprove, punish, kill}}
* {{och-l|咮|beak; to peck}}
* {{och-l|斸|to cut, cut out}}

The internet slang sense is a phonetic borrowing from {{bor|zh|en|true}}.

